caption: Came here for restaurant week. Excellent value for a three course prix fixe dinner. The lobster ravioli was amazing!
Table was an awkward size for the space it was in so we were leaning forward on the edge of our seat the whole time. Food was great though! Drinks were delicious also.

I had the pleasure of dining in last weekend, and the food was phenomenal! It's always exciting giving any new restaurant a shot. This establishment really went above and beyond with providing an experience for me and my date. The dominant factor of that experience went beyond the amazing food  and music. It started with the Service of our waitress, named Alex. Often times you try new restaruants and i don't know if its just my luck or what, but the service is rather lack luster in most cases. That was definitely not the case here, as we were made right at home soon as we walked through the door, and felt as if we'd been there ten times before. We really want to recognize Alex and her service especially  for how busy it was that night. Thanks again, see you guys soon!
The food was great!! Every single cocktail tasted great.

Looked nice, big menu, seems like other people like it. We went for dinner on a Wednesday, but left before ordering. They have a $20 valet for their lot, and only a very few pubic spots on Elston. Walked in, the music was pounding. They have a whole bottle service menu. I got the feeling that they are (or want to be) a nightclub. Just was not the vibe we wanted for a Wednesday dinner, and I did not get the feeling that a place with that focus would also have good food. We went to Alegrias.
Food was amazing, excellent service from Leo, highly recommend this place, you will not be disappointed.
Nice ambiance, good drinks. A good spot to go to for Restaurant Week. Be warned: you get a lot of food! And it's good!
Alejandra and Leo are phenomenal! Food is delicious and drinks are great
Service is great, food a bit slow but they make up for it personality. Great drinks, delicious food, and Leo/Alejandra are AMAZING. Will come again.
Love this place, music is amazing, food is great, highly recommend!!! Leo and Alejandra are the best!
Great food, awesome vibes, and Alexandra/ Leo!!

This restaurant spoke to my SOUL!! Reggaetón blasting, delicious, beautiful drinks and great service. They give you little drink samples as you walk in which I thought was adorable. I had the lobster roll which actually had a good amount of lobster in it. It was delicious!

First time and this place was amazing!!   The team did a great job here with the Mexico/Kiki’s on the River vibe.   Our server was Alejandra and she was amazing!!    Top notch customer service to rival Nobu, Gianni’s, and Tao.   I was damn impressed with the service and the food was great.  I just came from Mexico so my Latin pallet is more refined than normal.   Can’t wait to come back!!!
Tacos are great!
Great service and the food was delicious! I sure will be back again and again and again 🙂
Music was kinda loud , decent vibes tho

I’m not even going to lie about this place hand down one of the best places I have been too the food is super amazing and the drinks omg love it the place alone is beautiful I can’t wait to go again the owners of this place make sure your drinks and food are correct
Delicious food! Amazing drinks! Wonderful servers and bartenders! And some river views! This place has it all!
Very nice
Awesome atmosphere, amazing drinks, great service, nice views of the river. Prices are the same as average drinks downtown, but an atmosphere.
Love this place! Especially their welcome drinks and the main dish with pineapple and grilled lobster was so yummy.
Absolutely delicious and great service..my second time here and will continue to come back . Food is just so good
Best food in area
Not really into Mexican foods, but I enjoyed everybit of my brunch here. Very tasteful .
The drinks are delicious. The ceviche is good but the Pozole de Cameron is AMAZING!!

This place kind of caught me off guard at first I was skeptical of what type of cuisine that have however I was very intrigued and very drawn in with the shrimp, And really all seafood. The staff were so nice and awesome we even got two free round of shots out of it. The ceviche was off the chain, This is definitely a place you wanna go on the weekend so just let loose and enjoy a few drinks and eat great food!
Great food and service
We had such a fun time at Azul! We were greeted with tasty shots and our waitress was very friendly. The music was great, the food was tasty, and overall just a great vibe!

So I went here on a Saturday a couple weeks ago. The place appeared nice and Romantic ambiance. Our server was Yula and she was really nice up front. We were taking our time with menu and trying decide between drinks. Most of what they offer are straight drinks(typical 12-15 bucks) mixed drinks(15.00)and pitchers(60.00)We asked Yula about about tequila and she immediately says we have something that is great but cheaper than the prices listed and we were ok ordering two doubles. We ordered the fonduisa and chicken/steak/shrimp tacos. The fonduisa was burnt at bottom with chorizo stuck to the bottom of skillet and greasy. The shrimp was overcooked and over seasoned on top of chorizo. So not really great but moving on to tacos. There was nothing much to them. Meat lettuce and cilantro nothing spectacular. So we finished the food and was ready for bill. Yula comes to us and says BEFORE we even see the bill that she is going to ask the manager to come over to see if he can do something about the bill. Odd right...so I open it up and to my huge surprise we have been charged 144.00 for 2 double shots of tequila. The manager on cue walks over and says he can’t do anything about it and pretty much dismissed the fact that we were mislead by the waitress. I asked what tequila I purchased and he wouldn’t tell me at all. It literally tasted like casamigos anejo which an entire fifth is 47 bucks!. I had more than enough  to pay this ridiculous overcharged attempt at a “meal. Please make sure to ask up front what drinks your are being served or charged for. I was charged more for two drinks than 2 entrees and appetizer and those where not even worth the 64.00 dollars. Lesson learned. I would not recommend this restaurant. The food is mediocre and the information provided by our server was misleading. Lesson Learned. Will post receipt.
Amazing drinks, food n service!

I’m not sure how this place has so many good reviews. The place is nice inside and has a nice atmosphere. The michaeladas were good but were $15 each. Our bill was $200 for two of us with only 3 michaeladas. The food was however awful we didn’t even eat our dinner. The steak was terrible bad no flavor. Bottom line we won’t be going back there to eat. I give it two stars because of the drinks and atmosphere.

Such a great restaurant. The food was delicious and the service was excellent. The DJ played great music, which kept us all swaying our heads during dinner. I strongly recommend the camarones a la diabla, the spicy pomegranate margarita, and the palomas.
Excellent food and great drinks

I made a reservation for Azul for my birthday, 1/10.  I invited 5 of my girlfriends since COVID restrictions don’t allow reservations more than 6 people.  I’m not even sure how I found this restaurant, but I’m thinking it was through Opentable, since that’s how I made the reservation.  After checking out the restaurant’s website, I was sold.  The website is so vibrant and exciting and immediately made we want to visit.  There were many options on the brunch menu for my friends with shellfish allergies and vegetarians. When I arrived for my reservation, our temperatures were checked on our wrist and we were shown to our table.  They had small cards on the table with the QR barcode to scan and see the menu.  As we sat down, the waiter / bartender Leo handed us welcome drinks (cranberry sangria).  He was very attentive and brought welcome drinks over whenever anyone new from my party arrived.  We ordered several drinks including the margarita flight that came in small patron bottles as well as a pitcher of the mango margarita.  We also ordered some chips and salsa and guacamole for the table to share - and even though we requested separate containers for the salsa and guacamole for the 6 of us, they were quick to supply our every request.  Our entrees also came out quickly and everyone in my party enjoyed their food.  I had a friend who knew that I was going to be at the restaurant for brunch and she called them to set up a special birthday surprise with the manager.  I was brought out a brownie dessert with ice cream and a piñata filled with candy and a gift card.  My friend said that the manager was a pleasure to work with and I felt so special.  The treatment from all the staff was top notch and my friends and I plan on visiting Azul again very soon!!!  Also, the DJ they had that day was AMAZING...my friends and I had so much fun listening to great music.

Horrible food. The ceviche doesn’t have flavor. Needed more seasoning. The empanadas was ok but very overpriced. I had a Paloma. Worse drink I never had. Too much salt. The chilaquiles was not good at all. Nice venue but overprice food and bad food. Won’t be coming back.
Amazing
Great spot for  brunch or a weekend night out.
Food is ok but extra pricy, so expect to spend a good amount $$$$.
Stellar taco and seafood restaurant over near goose island that also has a great margarita selection with a lively atmosphere. There's also ample safe dining space for anyone looking to eat out
Great Latin flavor combination. You have to try the fantastic lobster tostones! Amazing cocktails and great outdoor space
Great cocktail list and awesome brunch

Restaurant Food and staff are great. Reason it gets 1 star though is they charge for parking in there large ample parking lot. They call it “valet” the guy doesn’t even valet it, just says park there... he’s useless. If you going to rip someone off to park at least valet it.
Great service ,but they need to improve the sazon in the  kitchen 🙄 and no using a lot sal in the soups.

I haven’t had so much fun for as long as I can remember. The staff here has all high energy and provides the best service. As we were enjoying our wonderful seafood dish, the manager offered us free lemon drop shots which really made the atmosphere alive. Thank you!
Very nice employees drinks are amazing!!!!! Good vibes all around!!! I recommend the passionfruit margarita with ceviche!!!
To pricey and I had better

We visited this establishment for the first time on 10/3/2020.  The ambiance and the drinks were great!!!  Not to mentioned the immaculate service we received from our waitress.(Tatiana) The only downfall was that we weren’t able to experience the outdoor view due to the inclement weather.  Nevertheless we’re definitely going back for the service, drinks, and hopefully the view. Thank you for the great experience.

(Translated by Google) It is the first time that I went with my friends, the prawns were my favorites, the cucumber margarita was delicious and the service was excellent, I will definitely return again  (Original) Es la primera vez que fui con mis amigas, los langostinos fueron mis favoritos, la margarita de pepino deliciosa y el servicio fue excelente, definitivamente regresare de nuevo
Food was okay from 1 to 10 I will say 8. Drinks cocktails are great.also bring some extra$$$$
Horrible experience! I was over charged and they where very unprofessional!

1st time and well the experience and atmosphere is great especially the service but the food was over priced especially for what we got, its not authentic marisco food it is really americanized, the drinks were ok, i did enjoy the empanadas 👍
Nice. I like the face lift.

Pros:  A sea-foodies delight with hot, cold and shareable options on the menu. Drinks are picturesque without sacrificing potency.  Rooftop & patio seating feature view of the river and the skyline. There is a dock, with a neighboring boat rental company on-site.  Cons: Valet parking or pay to park in their own lot - or free street parking on Elston.

This place was phenomenal.  The portions were very generous & the shrimp cocktail was the best I've had in a long time.  The Chipotle Cream Pasta was the best pasta I have had in a very long time.  The outside patio & rooftop make the experience even better.  Five stars & I can't recommend this restaurant enough.

I was excited to visit this place. The portion was smaller than the average I've tried. The piña rellena was filled with more pineapple than seafood, the corner booth where they seated us was too dark. The drinks were too soft and tasteless, it's a shame that they don't have frozen margaritas or any frozen drink. On the BRIGHT SIDE they let us go upstairs to enjoy the view for a little bit, and was pretty cool to see the city from up there.
Exquisite seafood and more, with the best views in Chicago!
(Translated by Google) The service very very good the food they use a lot of condiments but it's ok  (Original) El servicio muy muy bueno la comida usan muchos condiments pero esta bien
The food was great
The water guy won’t let your cup empty Say no more Great place Will be back Water guy good job 👌🏻💦
Great place! Miches are amazing! This place is a whole vibe the food is high scale and the music is a little bit of everything! The view is the best part! SERVICE IS 5 STARS!!!!!!!!!!
Fantastic. The newest local hidden gem for latin flavor and rooftop bar. Plus, a bonus for boat docking.
Excellent service, great environment, beautiful views, good music and delicious Latin inspired seafood. I totally recommend!!
Great location. Super friendly staff, everything tasted good.
Great menu, great staff!

We had dinner here on September 16, and overall it was a pleasant experience. It was relatively easy to find a reservation and valet is definitely a big plus.  The full menu was available on the rooftop due to the holiday, although there was a limited drink menu. The food took about 35 mins to get to us, and the server was great in checking in with us during this time.  We ordered langostinos, camarones a la diabla, and steak tacos. The langostinos were good and had the right amount of heat. The camarones were spicer. Steak tacos were fine, although very small.  There were no chips/salsa served while we waited for food. We did ask for tostadas to eat with our seafood and the server brought them out quickly. Overall, this is a different experience than typical mariscos place. It was nice and food was average. No huge complaints just wasn’t our cup of tea. There are better mariscos places in Chicago.
Great place to have some drinks with friends and family! King crab legs are amazing!

Glad we decided to check out this new spot that just opened. We were able to walk in and sit at the bar. I enjoyed the decor/art work. The staff and restaurant were respectful of Covid regulations, it also looked very clean. I had the lobster empeñadas and shrimp tacos, they were delicious. We had their special drink called El Grito and I also tried the paraíso. I highly recommend trying their specialty cocktails. Leo took care of us and was very friendly, made us feel welcomed. Matilde the manager stopped by and ensured we were having a good time. It’s obvious that they care about their hospitality and I’m excited to go back. Thanks Azul team!

It's early days for Azul, so this review may be very different when they work out some of the kinks,  but at the moment it seems to be having a bit of an identity crisis. It still feels like the club it used to be (albeit during covid-19 times), but it's trying to be a restaurant. We made dinner reservations and therefore expected to eat dinner; however, we were seated on the roof deck, which has lovely views of the river and skyline, but where apparently you cannot get entrees or good cocktails, so that's a waste of time for the dinner patrons and space for the proprietor. We made the best of it by ordering lots of apps and shared plates and got our own drinks from the downstairs bar. The food was hit or miss - the elotes were excellent, the guacamole, empanadas, and crab legs were good, the aguachiles were disappointing. I can't speak to the entrees because we couldn't order them. All in all, for the prices of the food, I would expect better execution all around. It is still a beautiful spot, so I hope they figure out how to make it a sustainable restaurant.

The service at this restaurant was okay, but the food somewhat made up for it. However, my experience here wasn't a good one at all. We dined in on a Sunday evening, for about an hour and a half. Went to our car only to find our window shattered and all of our belongings had been stolen out of our vehicle. Made 6 attempts to call 911, and only got through on the 7th attempt. I went inside and notified staff about my incident. However, it baffles me that although, they have a security guard that does rounds around the lot-- and a valet guy that SITS OUTSIDE &  no one heard or saw a thing? Apparently, there is also no cameras on the outside of the restaurant either. $800-$1k worth of items just taken out of my car right before 8pm on a Sunday and the restaurant seemed to not give a damn. Definitely will never be back & i URGE anyone considering this place to either uber or figure something else out.
(Translated by Google) Very nice place. But. The price. Very expensive. Why not. I like the food  (Original) El lugar muy bonito. Pero.  El precio. Muy caro. Xq no. Me gusto la comida

I wish I can give it 5 stars but they charged me 76.00 for 2 shots of Don Julio 1942.. I've never paid so much for tequila shots and I'm a tequila girl 👎🤷🏼‍♀️ the food was  good and its a nice location but the drinks are super pricey.
Great food.

Seafood lovers, you absolutely MUST check out this new spot in CHI! The lobster/Chihuahua cheese empanadas, stuffed pineapple and carne asada were on point. The shrimp ceviche....unbelievable! And, the service was impeccable - ask for Juan, the server. Two snaps and a twist to these two Chicago native, LATINO chefs who I'm sure we'll be seeing and hearing  a whole lot more about.#AzulMariscos #MariscosAutenticos
Nice place, to have a good time!

We went here for the first time Sunday and the food and service was great. Alejandra was an awesome waitress and had great recommendations and was very accommodating. Great atmosphere and great all around service. The Crab legs and the Langostinos(Prawns) were our favorites.

YUM! A beautiful spot right on the river with some of the most amazing seafood I’ve had in Chicago. My husband got the skirt steak and that was also delish. Really enjoyed it as a date spot and they were able to accommodate our baby and stroller.

DEFINITELY recommend checking this place out! It's a classy but fun oasis and i'm super impressed with how this group managed to transform this spot into something so cool in the middle of pandemic.  I went with a couple friends after dark last weekend, sat on the roof.  It was gorgeous; spacious, comfortable,  well-designed,  decor is on-theme but not overdone. Ample room to easily socially distance; and you see the staff working hard to make sure they're consistently cleaning.  Drinks were great.  Specialty cocktails were delicious, well presented, and packed a punch- and the rest of the beverage list has Latin-inspired drinks with a good balance of affordable and splurge-worthy stuff.  Food was stellar.  Seafood was fresh and well displayed and portioned/cut,  easy to eat socially.  The dishes were playful and unique but still very authentic.  Tons of surprising flavors.  (The burger was my personal fave, a perfect balance of chorizo and beef.)  Service was perfect.   Well staffed for the volume of the place, and super attentive; the team is clearly enjoying working there.  Atmosphere was amazing.  I've been to the building during previous operations (namely Estate) so I already knew it was a big unique spot with lots of potential;  so I was thrilled to see what they did to it. Roof was great, cabanas/high-tops/garden lights. The first floor/main bar/dining room area is a bright, art-filled, swanky space with multi-level/style seating and feels like it could be ocean-side instead of river-side.    From the roof we watched a few boats dock and come in for drinks.  This place is a great spot for families,  casual eats/drinks,  big nights out, and everything in between, and has the space for it.
The service and food were exceptional.  Great experience!

Great ambiance and service from the front door with temp wrist checks to the bar service and table dinner service.  Server very knowledgeable and proper PPE. Music was grooving on the spectacular roof top with views of the downtown skyline.  Management checked in multiple times  to make sure dinning experience was on par.  Thanks for the round of shots Rob! 😁
Great service great food great music awesome atmosphere
The smokiness prevalent in the dishes add such an great and unexpected kick. Crab legs are precut and without the mess. Best seafood in Chicago right now!
Great place to dock your boat and grab some drinks!

I had a drink before my friends arrived.. after a 2 hour boat ride we ate here afterwards.. Service was great! Cocktails wonderful! Food amazing! I had the grilled king crab legs with a side of rice and was soooo satisfied! The other people I was with had no complaints at all about their food! They have a nice spacious rooftop deck that is really enjoyable on a nice day with a nice view! I will most definitely be back here !
Great customer service, awesome food! Right next to a boat business, highly recommend! Matilde and Juan Really helped us out!
Great food, drinks and customer service.  Dock & Dine  is the Best.  Came up with my boat and they took care of us right away.  Will be returning soon...
Food, staff & view was amazing!
The Best Skirt Steak and Langostinos.
Somewhat overpriced for the quality of food, the chef is not very skilled that could be a factor as well. The meat was aweful.

I have always loved this location. I am happy to see that this spot has been revived and its better than ever! It's truly everything, from the bright colors, beautiful decor, creative interior paint, and carefully selected cocktails and seafood options. We enjoyed the lobster  empanadas and the shrimp ceviche. Both fresh and delicious. I can appreciate the concerns of COVID-19, so much so, that I too, am very selective about where/when I go out and the conditions. But in terms of Azul, you can't beat the cleanliness and the precautions they take; we felt safe here. To that end, if your familiar with the location, it's perfect. Outdoor space and a rooftop situated on the Chicago River. Brilliant. P.s., pontoon rental takes place here as well. All around a gr8t time! :p

I recommend even though in its current form it only opened two days before I went.  It describes itself as "Latin inspired seafood".  My wife and I both had the grilled salmon.  It had just the right amount of heat and flavor added.  Some  Latin places overdue the jalapenos but they got it just right.  The drinks were interesting.  The service was attentive and friendly.  The place is located on the river just across the bridge from Goose Island.  Upstairs they have a lounge deck they are planning to renovate for next year.  Wonderful views of the city.

Wow! Best new Marisco (seafood) place in town. Honestly the dishes we had were full of flavor and very innovative. This place had a nice ambiance, great music selection and most importantly besides food amazing and authentic drinks. I would highly recommend. Our servers were very friendly and available. Glad we gave it a shot!
Great decorations and outdoor seating. Fun Latin beachy vibe. Good cocktails and seafood (including a tequila honey glaze on the salmon!).

Visited Azul last night with my husband. Let’s talk about the detail and decor every corner of Azul has! Wow! Previous home to ESTATE and a whole new vibe and spark that absolutely ties up the name and menu so perfectly together. We sat in the Captain's Room. Everyone diligently wears their mask and gloves and impressive way of following all the rules for COVID including temperature check and properly distance seating and tables. We ordered a few drinks - the Cantarito which is a true representation in taste and The Paraíso which has a delicious rim of ground espresso beans. I ordered the Piña Rellena (Stuffed pineapple with octopus, lobster, shrimp, grilled pineapple, chipotle cream sauce, topped with melted chihuahua cheese) and my husband ordered the Langostinos. OH EM GEE the presentation speaks volumes and the taste? Out of this world! Both absolutely delicious! Great menu, amazing experience, and super excited to come back and try the Seafood Tower!
Good food! Phenomenal service! Beautiful place!!!!

I definitely recommend this place, i was there Thursday night. Thanks Beto Gutierrez for the introduction to this fresh delicious place.. staff is amazing and hard working.. my wife, my baby and i ate so much. those empanadas de lobster , Ceviche de camaron, Salmon. cantaritos , guava margarita and Langostinos were really good.. we're definitely coming back for the mariscada next.. 🥰

Amazing food and beautiful location. Perfect atmosphere for a nice date night or a business gathering. The staff and management are both extremely accommodating. I can’t say enough about this gorgeous establishment.
